OL,3,CResidents of small Welsh town fear
OL,4,C'HGV driving through every two minutes'
OL,6,FResidents of a small town in Rhondda
OL,7,FCynon Taf are protesting against the
OL,8,Fproposed expansion of a local quarry,
OL,9,Farguing the number of lorries
OL,10,Ftravelling on the main road is already
OL,11,Fputting them at risk.
OL,13,FPeople in Pontyclun argue the plans,
OL,14,Fif approved, would mean more traffic,
OL,15,Fas well as more dust and disruption.
